The second leg of Johnnie Walker GP Karting championship started this weekend at The Great Rift Valley (TGRV) circuit in Mai Mahiu. Seventeen teams battled out for the opportunity of a lifetime to watch a live Formula 1 race in Etihad Airways, Abu Dhabi. Sam Karangatha of Team Sim-U-Nation topped the races after recording the best time of 1.11.438. The teams had to complete six laps in a 10-minute circuit tucked in the archipelago of Rift Valley.